## Security Hardening -- Phase 3

Additional hardening: rate limits, CSRF origin validation, and session hardening.

### Changes

- **Rate limiting for calendar endpoints**
  - calendar/sync -- calendarSync preset (10/min)
  - calendar/connect -- calendarConnect preset (10/min)
  - calendar/disconnect -- calendarDisconnect preset (10/min)

- **Rate limiting for onboarding endpoints**
  - onboarding/open-term -- openTerm preset (20/min)
  - onboarding/accept-term -- acceptTerm preset (20/min)
  - onboarding/submit-review -- onboardingSubmitReview preset (5/5min)

- **CSRF origin validation**
  - New lib/http/csrf.ts -- validates Origin/Referer against APP_BASE_URL
  - Applied to calendar sync, connect, and disconnect endpoints
  - Relaxed in development, enforced in production

- **Session hardening**
  - All authenticated API routes now consistently use getUser() only
  - No getSession() fallback anywhere in server code

### Validation

- tsc --noEmit passes
- npm run lint passes
- npm run test:unit passes
